<div style="width: 740px; border: 1px dashed gray; padding: 10px;  margin:0px auto;">

<h2>Allotment of Married Accommodation for Airmen</h2><hr />
<span class="title">Screen Overview </span><br />
This screen will capture for Allotments of SMQ for Airmen.
<br /><hr /><br />
<img src="images/ma_allotmentmarriageaccomod.jpg" width="725"  /><br /><br />
<hr />

<p>
<span class="title">Pool Code:</span><br />
User can select the pool code from the given list, this will come from pool code screen, it will display only airmen pools and rank wise .It can't remain blank.
Based on selection of pool code all vacant SMQs list and pending register airmen list will display.

<br />
<span class="title">Allotment order file No:</span> <br />
It is system generation number, user can’t change number.
<br />
<span class="title">Allotment order file Date:</span> 
<br />It is system generated date, user can’t change date and it is present date.
<br />
    <span class="title">GRID (Display): </span> 
    <br />Based on search criteria data will display in the form of table. All pending registration details will display with Registration No, Registration Date, Service No, Service person name, And rank.
    
    <br />
    <span class="title">SMQ No:</span> 
    <br />User can select the SMQ No from the given list, this will come from SMQ screen, and it will display all vacated SMQ’s list. It can't remain blank.
    <br />
    <span class="title">Type of Allotment:</span> 
    <br />User can select from list, it contains 1) TMQ / Non Status, 2) Status, 3) Medical Grounds 4) Admin Grounds and 5) Retention
    <br />
    <span class="title">Retain Till:</span> 
    <br />If user select type is Retention then user should write retain date.
    <br />
    <span class="title">Allotment Date:</span> 
    <br />It is system generated date, user can’t change date and it is present date.
    <br />
    <span class="title">HO/TO Date:</span> 
    <br />It is system generated date, user can’t change date and it is present date.
    <br />
    <span class="title">Remarks:</span> 
    <br />User can write remarks and observations.
    <br />
    <span class="title">Save (Button):</span> 
    <br />By clicking on save button user can save the data. 
    <br />
    <span class="title">Reset (Button):</span> 
    <br />Clicking on reset button, will clear the current or existing data.
    <br />
    <span class="title">All.Order (Button):</span> 
    <br />Clicking on Allotment order button, user can print allotment order details.

</p>

</div>
